Astra, Bakrie Sumatera, Berau Coal: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-08-18T01:38:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/astra-bakrie-sumatera-berau-coal-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  fell 0.2 percent to 3,953.28.
The market was closed yesterday for a public holiday.  PT Astra International (ASII IJ): The country’s vehicle
sales rose 27 percent in July from a month earlier to 89,056
units, the highest monthly sales this year, Kontan reported,
citing Jonfis Fandy, marketing director at PT Honda Prospect
Motor. Sales in the first seven months of the year rose 14.5
percent to 506,743 units, the report said. Astra, Indonesia’s
biggest automotive retailer, was unchanged at 70,000 rupiah.  PT Bakrie Sumatera Plantations (UNSP IJ): The company had
its B-  credit rating  placed on “creditwatch negative”
yesterday by  Standard & Poor’s , which cited longer-than-
anticipated negotiations by the Indonesian company for a bank
loan to refinance notes maturing on Nov. 1. Bakrie Sumatera, a
palm oil and rubber producer, fell 1.3 percent to 385 rupiah.  PT Berau Coal Energy (BRAU IJ): The company’s first-half
net income rose to $76.4 million from $17.1 million a year
earlier, the Indonesia’s producer of power-station coal said in
a statement published in  Bisnis Indonesia . Berau advanced 2
percent to 520 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  